{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassProtocol\/addPrivate(privateSize:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"title":"addPrivate(privateSize:)","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject17TypeClassProtocolPAAE10addPrivate11privateSizeySi_tF","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"addPrivate","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"privateSize"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","platforms":[],"extendedModule":"GLibObject"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassProtocol"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Registers a private structure for an instantiatable type."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeclassprotocol\/addprivate(privatesize:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addPrivate"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"privateSize"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When an object is allocated, the private structures for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the type and all of its parent types are allocated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sequentially in the same memory block as the public"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"structures, and are zero-filled."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the accumulated size of the private structures of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a type and all its parent types cannot exceed 64 KiB.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function should be called in the type’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" function."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The private structure can be retrieved using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_TYPE_INSTANCE_GET_PRIVATE()"},{"type":"text","text":" macro."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The following example shows attaching a private structure","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MyObjectPrivate to an object MyObject defined in the standard","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"GObject fashion in the type’s "},{"code":"class_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note the use of a structure member “priv” to avoid the overhead","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of repeatedly calling "},{"code":"MY_OBJECT_GET_PRIVATE()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":["typedef struct _MyObject        MyObject;","typedef struct _MyObjectPrivate MyObjectPrivate;","","struct _MyObject {"," GObject parent;",""," MyObjectPrivate *priv;","};","","struct _MyObjectPrivate {","  int some_field;","};","","static void","my_object_class_init (MyObjectClass *klass)","{","  g_type_class_add_private (klass, sizeof (MyObjectPrivate));","}","","static void","my_object_init (MyObject *my_object)","{","  my_object->priv = G_TYPE_INSTANCE_GET_PRIVATE (my_object,","                                                 MY_TYPE_OBJECT,","                                                 MyObjectPrivate);","  \/\/ my_object->priv->some_field will be automatically initialised to 0","}","","static int","my_object_get_some_field (MyObject *my_object)","{","  MyObjectPrivate *priv;","","  g_return_val_if_fail (MY_IS_OBJECT (my_object), 0);","","  priv = my_object->priv;","","  return priv->some_field;","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"add_private is deprecated:"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use the G_ADD_PRIVATE() macro with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_DEFINE_*","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"family of macros to add instance private data to a type"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/TypeClassProtocol":{"title":"TypeClassProtocol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An opaque structure used as the base of all classes."}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypeClassProtocol"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassProtocol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeclassprotocol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TypeClassProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject","abstract":[],"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","title":"GLibObject","type":"topic"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/TypeClassProtocol/addPrivate(privateSize:)":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"addPrivate(privateSize:)","deprecated":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassProtocol\/addPrivate(privateSize:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"k